         <div>
            <head>10.8.1885 Montag</head>
            <p>
               <placeName type="write" key="49289">Rigi</placeName>
               <orgName key="49369">Kaltbad</orgName>. August 10. 1885
      Monday</p>
            <p>Worked at the Känzli in the morning. In the
      afternoon walked down to Romiti Felsenthor with
      <persName key="103">Mamma</persName> and <persName key="1863">Valentin</persName>. Very
      nice walk. The Felsenthor very interesting. The people at
      the <orgName key="67190">Felsenthor Hotel</orgName> were horrified at our asking for two
      lemons for lemonade, so <persName key="1863">Valentin</persName> and I had beer and only
      <persName key="103">Mamma</persName> lemonade. At the station met
      <persName key="1867">mother Goose (Miss Ricardo)</persName> as <persName key="1863">Valentin</persName>
      calls her. When we wanted to get in a fat old man came pushing up, and
      with a good tang in the ribs asked me &#x201e;Ob ich dächte dass ich
      allein da wäre&#x201c; &#x201e;Oh nein! sie sind jedenfalls dick genug
      dass man sie sieht&#x201c; About this all the Swiss people in the carriage were
      horrorstricken and made remarks and when <persName key="1863">V.</persName> gave it them
      one man nearly got a stroke. Beautiful Alpenglühen, the Jungfrau
      magnificent. After dinner spoke with <persName key="1863">Valentine</persName> about the
      <placeName key="x">Göschenen</placeName> tour. He did not seem to approve of it. Over
      1500 people died in Spain the day before yesterday.</p>
